If disable NAT, enable NAT, then disable NAT again Syncthing will crash. The reason is that we repeatedly add and remove the service from a supervisor, which isn't a supported pattern since a service shouldn't be restarted after it's been explicitly stopped. ~~We should create a new service instead.~~ Oh man that thing is wired deeply into the connection stuff. Probably we need to not stop the entire service but just tell it to lay low?

Sentry Issue: [SYNCTHING-MS](https://sentry.syncthing.net/syncthing/syncthing/issues/683/?referrer=github_integration)

